
# üåü SQLWithIDC ‚Äì Day 8 Challenge

## üß© **Challenge Question**
Create a patient summary that shows patient_id, full name in uppercase, service in lowercase, age category
(if age >= 65 then 'Senior', if age >= 18 then 'Adult', else 'Minor'), and name length. 
Only show patients whose name length is greater than 10 characters.

## üíª **SQL Query**
SELECT patient_id,UPPER(name) AS Full_Name,LOWER(service) AS Service_Name,CASE WHEN age >= 65 THEN 'Senior'WHEN age >= 18 THEN 'Adult'
ELSE 'Minor'END AS Age_Category,LENGTH(name) AS Name_Length FROM patients WHERE LENGTH(name) > 10;

üß† **Explanation**
* `UPPER(name)` ‚Üí Converts each patient‚Äôs name to uppercase.
* `LOWER(service)` ‚Üí Converts the service name to lowercase.
* `CASE` ‚Üí Categorizes patients into **Senior**, **Adult**, or **Minor** based on age.
* `LENGTH(name)` ‚Üí Finds the number of characters in each name.
* `WHERE LENGTH(name) > 10` ‚Üí Filters only those with long names.

## **Practical Questions**
**1Ô∏è‚É£ Convert all patient names to uppercase.**
SELECT patient_id,UPPER(name) AS Full_Name FROM patients;
  
**2Ô∏è‚É£ Find the length of each staff member's name.**
SELECT staff_id,staff_name,LENGTH(staff_name) AS Name_Length FROM staff;

**3Ô∏è‚É£ Concatenate staff_id and staff_name with a hyphen (-) separator.**
SELECT staff_id,staff_name,CONCAT(staff_id, '-', staff_name) AS Staff_Details FROM staff;

